text: Mr Anderson, I am the cashier that waited on your wife that morning. First of all, I need you to understand I wasn’t ignoring her. You forgot to mention the customer that I was talking with when you pulled up. The conversation we were having was work related, and you forgot to mention your wife waited less than a minute for me to take care of her. You also forgot to mention that your wife was trying to shut you up when you came in yelling and cursing at me. You also forgot to mention when you were cursing at me all I said to you was sir please leave the store. Not that it’s your business but I chose 3rd shift. My customers are my number one priority. I take my job very serious when it comes to my customers. I don’t like  that you’re unhappy,but I also know everyone can’t be pleased. I know you said your wife was disabled... maybe you should try getting out for her next time if 1 minute is too much time for her to be up.  You sure were able to get out to cuss me out. I don’t like that you’re unhappy with me, but I’ve done nothing wrong. Don’t know what else to say. Have a great day and “Take it easy”.

She says that she needs to have them INCASE someone else wants to purchase them.   Tell me why would you refuse to sale any items in a store that is there to be sold in the first place. We have six tobacco users in my home. And three of the members are guys so they dip and smoke. I promise you that you may not miss one sale but the couple of hundreds of dollars we spend a week is gone. I was understanding the many times I have gone in and they didn’t have enough there. But I asked them to please order so many cans for my hubby and we would buy them every other week. He is a OTR driver and preferred to give his money to the town we live in

text: This is an authentic Chinese restaurant, specialized in Chinese food. They cook rice and soup in a real Chinese style. I order my breakfast and lunch here five times every week. I think there are some American dude, they are sesame chicken kind of people, but come to this restaurant, asking the chef cook traditional Chinese noodle soup in a sesame chicken style. Sorry, it is cannot be done. This is a A+ restaurant for real Chinese dish. Specially, like Chinese breakfast bun, we call it “Bao Zi". Remember Auburn, before you go into a business, you should know what kind thing they offer and what kind thing you like. In a small town like Auburn, we all are lucky have this restaurant here. Their price is good, food good and close to campus. Thank you, your hard work means a lot to Auburn.

I had an arm full of stuff to purchase and he wasn't at a register when I approached so I unknowingly sat the items at the wrong one. When he eventually sauntered over instead of helping me move the items to the correct one, he just pointed and approached it and staired at me while I moved everything. I didn't mind having to move my stuff but, in my eyes, proper customer service would dictate the employee assist in moving everything because I had no idea I was at the incorrect register when I sat the things down. He also was not wearing a mask, even though there is a sign on the doors saying "masks required inside this facility".

Anyway, maybe I'm just being petty, but it just irked me the wrong way, him with his superior attitude and all. In the grand scheme of things im sure my contributions won't be missed, but treating people in the manner he did me will eventually lead to more people never returning. Management of this facility should probably look for some workers with at least a small amount of pride in their job. I get its only a fuel station attendant job but all jobs, especially ones dealing with the public, should show a little pride in their work and make the customer feel welcome.
